usage: Collections of command-line functions to perform common pre-processing and analysis functions.
       [-h]
       {getchr,sampfa,exseq,getscaf,seqsize,filsize,subnuc,basrat,genome_ranges,get_homopoly,asstat,plthist,gfftrans,vcfdp,gffsort,getcol,bamcov,pbamrc,ppileup,splitbam,smprow,gfatofa,faline,shannon,asmreads,mapbp,plotal,fachrid,runsyri,bam2coords,syriidx}
       ...

positional arguments:
  {getchr,sampfa,exseq,getscaf,seqsize,filsize,subnuc,basrat,genome_ranges,get_homopoly,asstat,plthist,gfftrans,vcfdp,gffsort,getcol,bamcov,pbamrc,ppileup,splitbam,smprow,gfatofa,faline,shannon,asmreads,mapbp,plotal,fachrid,runsyri,bam2coords,syriidx}
    getchr              Get specific chromosomes from the fasta file
    sampfa              Sample random sequences from a fasta file
    exseq               extract sequence from fasta
    getscaf             generate scaffolds from a given genome
    seqsize             get size of dna sequences in a fasta file
    filsize             filter out smaller molecules
    subnuc              Change character (in all sequences) in the fasta file
    basrat              Calculate the ratio of every base in the genome
    genome_ranges       Get a list of genomic ranges of a given size
    get_homopoly        Find homopolymeric regions in a given fasta file
    asstat              Get N50 values for the given list of chromosomes
    plthist             Takes frequency output (like from uniq -c) and
                        generates a histogram plot
    gfftrans            Get transcriptome (gene sequence) for all genes in a
                        gff file. WARNING: THIS FUNCTION MIGHT HAVE BUGS.
    vcfdp               Get DP and DP4 values from a VCF file.
    gffsort             Sort a GFF file based on the gene start positions
    getcol              Select columns from a TSV or CSV file using column
                        names
    bamcov              Get mean read-depth for chromosomes from a BAM file
    pbamrc              Run bam-readcount in a parallel manner by dividing the
                        input bed file.
    ppileup             Currently it is slower than just running mpileup on 1
                        CPU. Might be possible to optimize later. Run samtools
                        mpileup in parallel when pileup is required for
                        specific positions by dividing the input bed file.
    splitbam            Split a BAM files based on TAG value. BAM file must be
                        sorted using the TAG.
    smprow              Select random rows from a text file
    gfatofa             Convert a gfa file to a fasta file
    faline              Convert fasta file from single line to multi line or
                        vice-versa
    shannon             Get Shanon entropy across the length of the
                        chromosomes using sliding windows
    asmreads            For a given genomic region, get reads that constitute
                        the corresponding assembly graph
    mapbp               For a given reference coordinate get the corresponding
                        base and position in the reads/segments mapping the
                        reference position
    plotal              Visualise pairwise-whole genome alignments between
                        multiple genomes
    fachrid             Change chromosome IDs
    runsyri             Parser to align and run syri on two genomes
    bam2coords          Convert BAM/SAM file to alignment coords
    syriidx             Generates index for syri.out. Filters non-SR
                        annotations, then bgzip, then tabix index

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
